<subSubSection id="44911484C509BD48FF15FDED53F9FCED" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0C34470FC509BD48FF15FDED52A9FC86" blockId="25.[151,1437,577,1216]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FF15FDED5070FDEE" bold="true" box="[151,280,577,603]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Type data:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC509BD48FEA3FDED50D0FDEE" author="Friese, H." box="[289,440,577,603]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" pagination="117 - 120" refId="ref21703" refString="Friese, H. (1900) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Centris und Epicharis. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 117 - 120." type="journal article" year="1900">Friese (1900)</bibRefCitation>
proposed this species based on a single female collected by the Swiss mountaineer and writer Johann Jakob Weilenmann (1819‒1896). As a textile merchant, Weilenmann traveled to New York and then to 
<collectingRegion id="CE4F89EDC509BD48FF34FD25502DFD16" box="[182,325,649,675]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC509BD48FE64FD255346FD16" box="[486,558,649,675]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. During his stay in that country, Weilenmann created an extensive collection of insects, which he would later donate to the Zurich Polytechnic (
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC509BD48FC0CFD01550DFD72" author="Anonymous" box="[910,1125,685,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" refId="ref20788" refString="Anonymous (2018) Johann Jakob Weilenmann auf dem Piz Buin (3.312 m). Bergwelten Magazin TV Online. Available from: https: // www. bergwelten. com / a / johann-jakob-weilenmann-auf-dem-piz-buin- 3 - 312 - m (accessed 14 February 2020)" type="url" year="2018">Anonymous, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Between the samples collected there was the specimen used by Friese to describe this species. The 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC509BD48FC50FD7D555CFD5E" box="[978,1076,721,747]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">holotype</typeStatus>
is housed at 
<collectionCode id="6A9ADFCAC509BD48FB47FD7E546AFD59" box="[1221,1282,722,748]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
and it has the following data label: Pernambuc. Weilenmann [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FC95FD5A554EFCA5" authority="Fr." authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1900" box="[791,1062,757,784]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weilenmanni">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FC95FD5A5568FCBA" box="[791,1024,757,784]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Centris weilenmanni</emphasis>
Fr.
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount id="1A8D8C86C509BD48FBAEFD5A5529FCA5" box="[1068,1089,758,784]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
[handwritten] 1910 Friese det. [printed]\ [red label] Type [printed]\ Zool. Mus. Berlin [printed] (
<collectionCode id="6A9ADFCAC509BD48FCF0FCB552DCFC86" box="[882,948,793,819]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
