<subSubSection id="44911484C509BD48FF45FCCD5081FB75" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0C34470FC509BD48FF45FCCD5081FB75" blockId="25.[151,1437,577,1216]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FF45FCCD502FFCCE" bold="true" box="[199,327,865,891]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Comment:</emphasis>
This is the rarest species of 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FD0BFCCE53B3FCC9" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[649,731,866,892]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FD0BFCCE53B3FCC9" box="[649,731,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Centris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by Friese. 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FC4FFCCE55DEFCCE" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1900" box="[973,1206,865,892]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weilenmanni">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FC4FFCCE55DEFCCE" box="[973,1206,865,892]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Centris weilenmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type specimen which is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FDF2FC2A52E7FC2A" authority="Snelling, 1966" authorityName="Snelling" authorityYear="1966" box="[624,911,901,928]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolae">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FDF2FC2A53EBFC15" box="[624,643,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FD12FC29538DFC2A" box="[656,741,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">carolae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC509BD48FD68FC2952E7FC2A" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[746,911,901,927]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref23464" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1966) The taxonomy and nomenclature of some North American bees of the genus Centris with description of new species (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 112, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1966">Snelling, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC509BD48FB3FFC29545EFC2A" box="[1213,1334,901,927]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="749C079FC509BD48FADAFC2951D9FC71" name="Mexico" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="681A3AFEC509BD48FF3DFC0550E5FC76" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[191,397,937,964]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref22678" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FE90FC06502BFC76" box="[274,323,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). This latter species is relatively infrequent to be found in collections, and the females of both species differ almost exclusively in details of the coloration and pubescence. On the other hand, Pernambuco state, as well as most of the neighboring states (Paraíba (north), Ceará (northwest), Alagoas (southwest), Bahia (south), and Piauí (west)) have been received numerous collecting activities for several decades, but a single specimen of this species has never been collected.A possibility could be that the 
<typeStatus id="D330F9ADC509BD48FC07FB95528FFBE6" box="[901,999,1081,1107]" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">holotype</typeStatus>
was mislabeled and it was actually collected in Central America. In this case 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FDCBFBF253D7FBC2" authorityName="Snelling" authorityYear="1966" box="[585,703,1117,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolae">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FDCBFBF25334FBCD" box="[585,604,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FDE8FBF153D7FBC2" box="[618,703,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">carolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be proposed as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FB18FBF2542CFBC2" box="[1178,1348,1117,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weilenmanii">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FB18FBF255C5FBCD" box="[1178,1197,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FB39FBF1542CFBC2" box="[1211,1348,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">weilenmanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the differences between them could be only variation. Unfortunately, nothing is known about the variation of coloration and pubescence of 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B3C8CC509BD48FEEFFB0A508AFB0A" authorityName="Snelling" authorityYear="1966" box="[365,482,1189,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolae">
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FEEFFB0A50E8FB75" box="[365,384,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3EFF9B1DC509BD48FE0CFB09508AFB0A" box="[398,482,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="256">carolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
